6:
Damn... monster... Just how strong...
IS he?
10:
Stars above, turn your cold
countenances upon the creatures
below, who beg scraps of your
heavenly light.
15:
Know the weight of their wishes.
Know the gravity of your failures.
Know, that you shall fall!
28:
Come, Stella. The elf's gust cannot
have carried them far.
38:
I created an explosion to blast us
away, then Estariel called the wind
to fly us here.
41:
I did nothing so elegant. I merely
called the wind to break our fall.
42: We had no choice but to flee.
46: I couldn't even scratch him... I, I...
54:
Listen. We were outmatched. So we
ran. And we will KEEP running, if we
value our lives.
57:
Where are we supposed to run TO,
exactly?
66:
If we make it to Excelion and use the
Mark, we may yet have a chance!
67:
We can reclaim all the Lord of
Shadow stole from us!
71:
Hmm... He certainly won't let us waltz
into the keep. We need a plan.
79:
Adjudicus. Shall I just assume you
overheard everything?
83:
It's the fiend from the forest!
...Why do you know his name?
85:
I understand your suspicion, but this
man is not our enemy. Whether he is
an ally, however, is yet to be seen.
90:
Hmph. I come bearing Estariel's
cloaks. They are elven-made, and
will camouflage the wearer.
93:
Wait. What does a fiend get out of
aiding us?
96: I too aim to topple the Dark Throne.
98:
My mission is more important than
my personal grievances. Is yours,
Champion Light?
100:
Now, we must move. Take a cloak,
and stay on guard. Remember, the
invisibility is only a disguise—the
Lord of Shadow has other means of
sensing you.
107: Surely you don't expect me to run.
112:
Does a princess not belong with her
people? My subjects are in mortal
peril! I cannot simply abandon—
122: I must return to the base at once!
132:
I-I don't know! But I have a
responsibility to—
140: I'll carry her. Hand over the cloaks.
145:
What about Eric? He was still alive... I
have to... Ngh...
149:
I'll help Alk. And... Stella? I know how
stubborn you are, but... Please don't
make me do this Shakari's way.
Okay?
